{
  "text": "In a previous study (Smith & Yanagimachi, 1989) , we collected fertile spermatozoa from the isthmus of mated hamsters, but were not certain whether these spermatozoa had been bound to the mucosa. Presumably some of them may have been recovered from the lumen and others from the mucosa. In the present study ( [CITATION_1] and the results of the present study, suggest that the majority of eggs are probably fertilized by spermatozoa that temporarily attach to the isthmic mucosa during storage.",
  "citation_candidates": [
